{"/service/ndnp/nvln/batch_nvln_deeth_ver01/data/sn86076356/00332890414/1908042701/0857.xml":{"full_text":"THE SILVUR STATE NEWS\nCASE mi WRIGHT, MMm\nMondays and Thursdays at Wuuumacea Nevada\nEntered at the postoffice at Winnemncca for transmission through tie\nnails as second-class matter.\nSILVER STATE NEWS\u2014VOLUME 2 No. 6. SILVER STATE\u2014VOLUME\nXLIX, No. 33.\nOne Year $3.00: Six Months $2.00: Three Months $100.\nFinancial Conditions are Improving\nand Business Outlook is Much Brighter\nThe Republican party in Congress\nevidently intends to do everything\npossible at this sessio nto remodel the\nAmerican currency system, to break\nthe forceof the fniancial depression\nwhich exists throughout the nation,\nand to render impossible reoccurence\nof the distressing conditions which oc\ncurred during the last nine months\nto paralyze idnustrial enterprises be\ncaues funds were unavailable from\nany souree.\nAnd it is a noteworth fact, in the\nmeantime that the financial situation\nis gradually improving in the east,\nthat order is coming out of the chaos\nwhich reigned in Wall street, and that\nthe larest bankers of New York during\nthe last week undertook the export of\n$8,000,000 gold to European centers.\nWithin the same period there was\nannouncii) us having been recently\nnegotiated by the Pennsylvania rail\nroad company an European loan of\n$40,000,000 on bonds for betterments\nand improvements on that company's\ngigantic system.\nThese practical illustrations of a\nbetter feeling among the world \\s\nfinancier^ will certainly redound to the\nrapid recovery of the mining industry\nthroughaut the west, and especially in\nNevada, Idaho and Utah, which three\nstates have suffered the most from\nthe panic, because promoters and\noperators with projects partly under\nway were caught at the moat inoppor\ntune time for the completion of their\nnegotiations. And with the mining in\ndustry once more receiving its right\nful quota of the capital of the nation,\nevery other industry in Nevada wi..\nbe seen to blossom out anew.\nTne outlook is, therfore, that in\nstead of the intense depression of the\npast continuing until after the presi\ndential election, it will be scarcely so\nacutely felt by mid-summer\n(Nevertheless, the delays of the\nrepresentatives in Congress regarding\nthe financial reconstruction, which the\nrepublican party must carry though\nto success, are of intense interest to\nevery man having the welfare of the\ncountry and himself at heart. It\nmakes little difference whether he be\nRepublican or Democrat, each indivi\ndual wants the money system so ar\nranged that he may never again expe\nrience a panic.\nA conference on currency legisla\ntion was held last Thursday between\nthe House and Senate leaders, and was\nattended by Speaker Cannon and Sen\nator Aldrich. The judgment of the\nconference was that the program late\nly decided on should be put through.\nThis program called for a caucus of\nthe Republican members of the House,\nprobably this week, to determine the\npassage of a bill creating the needed\ncurrency bill and to investigate the\ncurrency cystem and the financial con\ndition of the country at large, and t\nreport on theremcdial legislation at\nthe next session of Congress.\nTt is further the desire of the Hous\nRepublican leaders to put through th\nVreeland bill, which embodies wha\nare thought to \"be the best feature\nof the Aldrich bill, and eliminates th\nprovisions to which most objection hni\nbeen made. All that the Senat\" lead\ners ask of the House leaders is t\nenact some piece of financial legisla\ntion, so that the Senate will have sonn\nmeasure to use as a working basis, al\nthought of enacting of the Aldrich bil\nin the form of whichit passed th*\nSenate having been abandoned.\nThe program is to have the Senate\nthen strike out everything after th*\nenacting clause in the House bill am\nto insert the Aldrich bill. This will\nhave theeffeet of throwing the amend\ned bill into conference and care will\nbe exercised both in the Senate and in\nthe House to appoint as confer\"*;*\nmembers who favor some legislation\nat this session.\nIt will be the task of the conferees\nto patch up from the Aldrich bill and\nVreeland bill and the commission bill\na modified act embracing such pro\nvisions as the leaders feel sure of put\nting through the two houses.\n-o\u2014\nBUILDING BOCK JETTIES.\nIn building the Galveston jetties,\nrock is transported for a long dis\ntance by rail ami loaded onto barges.\nThe barges are towed to the scene\nat operations, where a derrick barg\u2018\nswings them into position These big\nblocks of stone weigh several tot s\nuch.\n\u201cI have found out '.hat there is no\nuse to die of lung trouble as long as\nyou can get Dr. King\u2019s New Diseov\n?ry, savs Mrs. \u00bbT. P. White of Rush\naoro. Pa. \u201cI would not be alive today\nvut for that wonderful medicine. It\noosens up a cough quicke^ than any\nfhng else after the case is pronounced\ntopeless. This most reliable remedy\nFor coughs and colds, mgrippe, bron\n:hitis and hoarseness is sold under a\nguarantee at the Eagle Drug store. 50c\ntnd $1.00. Trial bottle free. mo\u00bb\n_\nCONSTITUTION\nFOR\nWOMAN S CLUB\n\n__________\nARTICUB 1.\nNAME.\nThe name of this asociation shall beho WOMAN\u2019S PERSONAL APPEARANCE Cl>l B.\nAKTICLjj U.\nX V OBJECT. t\nThe object of this association shall be the improvement of the personal appearance 'of each of its \"members\nARTICLE IU.\nMEMBERSHIP.\nSection 1.. Membership in the club shall be of two classes, Active and Passive.\nSection 2. Active membership shall be limited to those who intelligently devote a reasonable share of\ntheir time to the object of this association.\ni Section 3. Passive membership shall be confined to those who, while disinclined to investigate the opportu\nnities for personal improvement, are willing to accept the advice of those who do.\nARTICLE IV.\nOFFICERS.\nThe offices of President, First aud Second Vice Presidents Secretary and Treasurer shall be honorary in\ncharacter and mav be assumed at will bv members, when such assumpt inn advances the good of tin- cause.\nARTICLE V.\nMEETINGS.\nSection 1. Regular meetings may occur upon bright days, following the careful preparation of members\nfor the purpose.\nfSeetion 2. No member shall be admitted to any regular meeting w hose appearance does not instantly\nstamp her as a member of the club.\n'Section 3. Special or unexpected meetings between members may occur at any time or place, therefore,\neach member should be careful at all times of her membership, and never appear untidy or lie seen with dull,\nbrittle or unsightly hair.\nARTICLE VI.\nQUORUM.\nSection 1. One member shall constitute a quorum for the execution of any plan or the use of any pro\nphylatic not out of harmony with the object of the association.\niSection 2. Upon special occasions a large number may eonstiitucions a large number may constitute a\nquorum, provided the purpose of themeeting interests and instructs those who are known to be loval to the\nClub.\nARTICLE VII.\nSection 1. But one amendment is permissible under this constitution.\nSection 2. Article 111 may be amended by the addition of a section permitting auxiliary members.\nSection 3. Any married man may become an auxiliary member by promptly and cheerfully purchasing\n\u2014for his own family\u2014such toilet remedies or requisites as may be desired by any active or passive memher.\nIt is passing strange that we have no\nclubs for the improvement of one\u2019s\na personal appearance, \u201cto back a nn\nIII II I I ture club,\u201d so to speak. We certain\nNil ly need them for we all konw that\nllU I L I one lecture by a capable dermatolo\ngist would be more helpful to the\ncomplexion than a ton of beauty lo\ntion.\nNo one has other than encouragement\nfor literary clubs, but we are forced\n|i Ayr to admit that many many hours are\nu|| I I devoted to looking up the depredations\nN11 of some ancient buccaneer, when the\nI1LJ I L L time would be worth more if spent\nin combatting the depredations of the\ndandruff germ.\nUpon this very subject, how many\nknow about the dandruff germ, and\nthe havoc it creates with a luxuriant\nynTr n growth of hairl It is a deplorable\nN|| h K fact that up to within very recent\n|f U L U years, one century rolled after another\nwithout any important addition to our\nknowledge of hair preservation.\nNearly six thousand years ago, or to\nbe exact, 4000 B. C., the mother of the\nI Egyptian king, C'hata (second king of\nI the first dynasty) tried to save the\nhair of that monarch with a mixture\nof dog\u2019s paws, dates and asses\u2019 hoofs,\nt ground up and cooked in oil (Egyptian\nPapyrus). Similar remedies have been\npopular over since.\nI Just when cantharides took the place\nof dog\u2019s paws in hair remedies iy i it\nI known, but Hippocrates, 4 4 the father\nof medicine,\u201d used it four hundred\ni years B C., and it has been in con\nstant use\u2014ywith no benefit whatever\n1 up to within the present decade, '.lost\nI hair remedies contain it even now.\nI \u201cWhat is canthardest\u201d Simply a foul\nI smelling dead fly or bug from tha\nLevant, that has been dried, powdered\nand soaked in alcohol. The elder Pliny\nI A. D. 23, and also Dioscorides, over\nI come the \u201cmousy\u201d odor with hot\nI vinegar.\nIt remained for the eminent German\nInna (ask your doctor about him) ti\ndiscover that the real cause of the\ndandruff, the itching scalp and falling\nhair, is an invisible microbe growth\nof vegetable character that lodges and\ndevelops in the sebaceous glands of the\n1 air follicles in the scalp. This show\nthat the disease is contagious and als\nthat the use of dead animals or lmgr\nis worse than useless.\nHead wow a guinea pig was Jeundt'.\nhuir with human dandruff germs on\npage 511* \u201cJackson on Disea.ea et the\nr\u00bbsk.u,\u201d 4th editou. Also La cot, Hep\ntimber 24, \u201904, M/iJieil ll-v.-w of KV\nv i ws, New York, Nov \u201901; New\nKi gland Medical Monthly, Oct '0-:\nLiterary Digest, New ork. Mutch 1,\n2 and Nov. 12, v4.\nThe first remedy to succesfully coin\nbat the dandruff germ and stop itch\ning and permit the hair to grow as\nnature intended was Newbro\u2019s Herpi\neide. It is a scientific germicide and\nscalp prophylactic. It does not stain\nor dye the hair and it contains no\ncantharides. While Newbro\u2019s Herpi\ncide will not cure chronic eases of\nbaldness or do anything \u201cmagical,\u201d\nits intelligent use will produce results\nthat are, to say the least, extraordi\nnary. In addition to its remedial\nproperties it makes the hair light and\nfluffy, and gives it a silken gloss. J>r.\nV. T. McGillycuddy, Denver, Colorado,\nMedical Inspector Mutual uife Insu\nrance Company, New York, writes as\nfollows, concerning Newbro s Herpi\neide:\n\u201cKnowing the composition of Her\npieide 1 can state that it contains\nnothing injurious. In a great number\nof cases of baldness, a neglected dan\ndruff can be considered as its imme\ndiate exciting cause, or associated con\ndition. Your Herpicide will, in the\nvast majority of cases, cure and pre\nvent the continuation of dandruff. It.\nis an elegant aud ideal hair dress\niug.\nEagle Drug Company, Agents (or Newbro's Herpicide\nWhy Send Away\nWhen Clothes Can Be Had a!\nI. SCHLINGER\nTHE NEW TAILOR\n1 For the same money as for so-called\ntailor-made suits made in Chicago or\n1 San Francisco Chinese tailor-shop?\nTor the next two weeks a one third\nreduction on made-to-order clothes or\ndered from me.\nLadies\u2019 and Gents\u2019 Tailoring\nFit and Workmanship Guaranteed\nDIEHL t!\u00a3\nCentrally Located. Brig1* Sunny Rooms\nEvery attention for the accommodations\ngnests.\nWINNEMUCCA, NEVADA\nWASHING WITHOUT WATER\njs Like Trying to Got Rid of DudrmM\nWithout Herplclde.\nDid you ever see any one trying to\nwash themselves without ooap or\nwater?\nIf you did what would you say of\nhim?\nIt Is every bit as foolish to try to get\nrid of Dandruff and to prevent Bald\nness by feeding tbe germs which cause\nIt. with Cunthrartdes, Vaseline, Glycer\nine and similar substances which form\nthe principal ingredients of most so\ncalled Hair growers.\nNewbro\u2019s Herplclde Is successful be\ncause It attacks and kills the parasitic\ngerm which feeds on the hair roots.\nIt Is the original and only genuine\necaip germicide manufactured.\nBold by leading druggists. Send 10c. In\notamps for sample to The Herplclde Co.,\nDetroit, Mich.\nTwo sizes, 50c and fl.00, at Eagle Drug\nand Jewelry Company.\nFRATERNAL ORDERS\nL p. O. F.\nHUMBOLDT LODGE, NO.\n16, I.O.O.F.\u2014Meetings on\nthe 1st and 3d Thurs\nday evenings of each mcnth at hall\nm Silver State bnildirg. Visiting\nbrothers in good standing always\nwelcome.\nWm. OLIVER, N. G.\nFRANK RAMDOHR, See.\nMA^ONaC\nWINNEMUCCA LODGE, NO\n19, F. and A.M.\u2014Stated com A\nmunications will be held at\ntheir hall in the Silver State Wr'\nblock until further notice at 7:30 p\nm. on tke first Saturday evening ji\neach month. All Master Masons\ngood standing are cordially invited t\nattend. C L. TOBIN, W. M.\nCHRIS WOLF, Secretary\nHUMBOLDT CHATTER NO 9. A\nR. A. M.\u2014Meetings held at\ntheir hall at 8 p m. on the\nSec end and Fourth Saturday\nevenings of each month. AH Com\npanion Royal Arch Masons in good\nstanding are cordially invited to at\ntend. W. A. BROWN, H. P.\nCHRI8 WOLF, Secretary.\nO. E. S.\nSILVER STATE CHAPTER NO. 6.\n0. E. 8, meets in Silver State Hall\nat 7:30 p. m. on the 2d and 4th\nThursdays of each month. Vicit'u*\nmembers in good standing always\nwelcome.\nJENNIE PORTER, W. M.\nLUCY LAVEAGA. Sec\nNOTICE OF FORFEITURE.\nTo O. C. Sawyer, a ioownei with\nthe undersigned, of the Alvarado mine\nor mining claim, situated in the Ken\nnedy mining district, Humboldt conn\ntv. State of Nevada, notice of loca\ntion thereof being recorded in office\nof the County Recorder of said county\nin Book I of Notices, Page .'if. 